        Rethinking Tags:
             ✔ I've decided to redo the tags page... and by redo I mean remove altogether. Instead I have switched to using filters. The upside is that everything happens in one page and I don't need to worry about passing props an working with routes. It's a much simpler solution and uses 1 less call to the database. The major downside is that you can no longer directly go to a tag page. There is also more work being added to the news-item-loop-view. @started(16:02 - 05/04/21) @done(13:04 - 14/04/21) @lasted(1w1d21h2m26s)
                ✔ So i ended up doing this and then undoing in. The "news/weather/sports" now function as a filter on the home page. The author and postdate in article will use a modified version of the old tags method of using routes to pass props. @done(11:33 - 09/04/21)
                ✔ You can still go to "news" tag page via url params setting state. @done(11:34 - 09/04/21)
                ✔ I also have as many database calls as I did when I started. However, the new tags3.1 component is much more flexible by allowing you to access tag pages via articles or url all from one component. @done(13:04 - 14/04/21)
