                         I want to update the card but I need to update state to do that. I think the best way of doing that is to wrap the renderCard component in a stateful component that can handle state and update bookmarked status.
                             I've moved over to a stateful component to see if I can make this easier.
                                 No luck so far, I can update the array and state but the card controls don't update to reflect the new value. Not sure where to go from here. 
                                 I need this to work so I need to figure this out
                                 There's a a lot of things to consider here. Maybe try and recreate the issue in a smaller scale and work from there.
                                 3/8 - I've done it. You can now add or remove bookmarks using both the buttons and swiping.
                                     The solution was to use both a prop and state within the oncardcontrols and update them to match eatch other when clicking or gesturing.
                                     This involved lifting the state from the oncardcontrols file, into the new state based render card method.
                             Q: Having create the new component, do I actually need state for this??
                                A: I don't need the state but I do need the non-functional component for my code to work

