        ☐21/4/2021 - This is very annoying.
            ☐https://christopherdunne.co.uk/theKnews/home -- Doesnt work if you access directly
            ☐You need to go to - > https://christopherdunne.co.uk/theKnews/ and then click on the header to get to the actual website which is located at : https://christopherdunne.co.uk/theKnews/home
            ☐Solution - > I changed all of the routes from /home to /theKnews/home
            ☐Added a .htaccess to theKnews folder with the below code. The rewrite base and last rewrite rule need to match the folder the .htaccess file is in.

            <IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
                RewriteEngine On
                RewriteBase /theKnews
                RewriteRule ^index\.html$ - [L]
                RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
                RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
                RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-l
                RewriteRule . /theKnews/index.html [L]
            </IfModule>

